enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve setting up a loan with a collateral coin and require similar parameter checks.
Both methods involve repaying a loan, though the latter is more general and less flexible.
The output of flexibleLoanRepay can be verified by checking the repayment history, which is handled by flexibleLoanRepayHistory.
The repayment rate can be verified using collateralRepayRate, which provides the rate of collateral used for repayment.
